"Stealth Login\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://frosty.media/?p=226088\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:370:\"<p>Thanksgiving morning I jumped into some code and updated two Custom Login extensions that had not seen an update since December of 2014.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://frosty.media/2017/two-custom-login-extensions-updated/\">Two Custom Login extensions updated</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://frosty.media\">Frosty Media</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Austin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2977:\"<p>Yesterday, Thanksgiving morning I jumped into some code and updated two <a href=\"https://frosty.media/plugins/custom-login/\">Custom Login</a> <a href=\"https://frosty.media/plugin/category/extensions/\">extensions</a> that had not seen an update since December of 2014.</p>\n<h2>Updated Custom Login extensions</h2>\n<p>First update was <a href=\"https://frosty.media/plugins/custom-login-page-template/\">Custom Login Page Template</a> which received some code cleanup and tests against the latest Custom Login version including the recently released WordPress version <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2017/11/tipton/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">4.9</a>. Since the Page Template plugin integrates with <a href=\"https://frosty.media/plugins/custom-login-stealth-login/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Custom Login Stealth Login</a> that plugin got an update of the same caliber too.</p>\n<h3>Active licenses</h3>\n<p>If your license is current and active (and you&#8217;ve got the <a href=\"https://frosty.media/plugins/frosty-media-license-manager/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">license manager</a> plugin) you&#8217;ll receive an update notice in your WordPress admin dashboard. If you don&#8217;t have an active license anymore, you can easily login and update your license to grab the latest version. Speaking of new versions, the License Manger plugin has also received some updates in the last few weeks and is fully compatible with the latest WordPress version and all our plugins on the site. Check out the latest <a href=\"https://github.com/Frosty-Media/frosty-media/releases\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">releases</a> on GitHub.</p>\n<h3>What&#8217;s new in Custom Login Page Template?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Code cleanup (a lot).</li>\n<li>Add empty return value to the excerpt of the login page template.</li>\n<li>Remove the Login Page Template from search results.</li>\n<li>Add notice when Custom Login is missing.</li>\n<li>Update Frosty Media Requires to 1.0.4.</li>\n<li>Update TGM Plugin Activation to 2.6.1.</li>\n<li>Fix: non-object when using Custom Login Stealth Login with this plugin.</li>\n<li>Remove admin.js that&#8217;s not being used.</li>\n<li>Tested up-to WordPress 4.9.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What&#8217;s new in Custom Login Stealth Login?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Code cleanup (a lot).</li>\n<li>Remove unused CSS file and enqueue.</li>\n<li>Add notice when Custom Login is missing.</li>\n<li>Update Frosty Media Requires to 1.0.4.</li>\n<li>Update TGM Plugin Activation to 2.6.1.</li>\n<li>Fix: Change javascript enqueue id as to not clash with Custom Login&#8217;s.</li>\n<li>Fix: admin.js no-longer getting enqueued.</li>\n<li>Fix: admin.js correctly toggling fields on checkbox on/off in settings view.</li>\n<li>Tested up-to WordPress 4.9.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://frosty.media/2017/two-custom-login-extensions-updated/\">Two Custom Login extensions updated</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://frosty.media\">Frosty Media</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"Custom Login Style Pack no. 3 Released\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://frosty.media/2017/custom-login-style-pack-three-released/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 14 Nov 2017 17:00:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Custom Login\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://frosty.media/?p=224398\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:379:\"<p>It\'s been over two years since the